data-triple-N3.o: "The Daily News of New York City is the fourth most widely circulated daily newspaper in the United States. The first U.S. daily printed in tabloid form, it was founded in 1919, and as of 2013 is owned and run by Mortimer Zuckerman. It has won ten Pulitzer Prizes."@en
